---

# 9. Budget Management

The AI must allocate budget according to performance.

Rules:

Kill losers quickly  
Scale winners gradually  

Scaling rules:

Increase budget 10–20% every 24–48 hours.

Avoid sudden budget jumps.

Large increases reset learning phase.

---

# 10. Automation Rules

The AI must use automation.

Examples:

Pause ads if CPA exceeds threshold.

Scale ads if ROAS exceeds target.

Reduce budget if performance declines.

Increase budget if conversion rate increases.

Automation reduces human workload.

---

# 11. Creative Fatigue Detection

The AI must detect ad fatigue.

Symptoms:

Frequency rising
CTR falling
CPA rising

Solution:

Launch new creatives.

Creative refresh cycles:

7–14 days for high spend accounts.

---

# 12. Attribution Intelligence

The AI must understand attribution limitations.

Platforms do not see all conversions.

The AI must consider:

View-through conversions  
Multi-touch attribution  
Delayed conversions  

True performance often exceeds reported performance.

